  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Tender Manager, M&E Contractor",
  "description": "<ul><li>Lead and organize the preparation, review, and submission of tenders for mechanical, electrical, and ELV systems, ensuring completeness, quality, and compliance with technical and risk requirements.</li><li>Analyze and clarify RFQs during the pre-tender and tender phases, raising queries or amendments to influence clients or consultants where possible.</li><li>Consolidate and analyze technical data, bill of quantities, price schedules, and financial details to ensure compliance, mitigate risks, and maintain competitiveness during the tender process.</li><li>Coordinate project involvement during the tender phase, including manpower planning and preparation of a project organization chart and preliminary costs.</li><li>Enhance and consolidate quotes to meet target win prices, preparing a tender cost summary for management approval, and ensuring margin protection, while also preparing for tender interview presentations to support negotiations.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree/Diploma in Engineering/QS related studies</li><li>At least 5-7 years of working experiences in Quantity Surveying/Tender Management for M&E Contractor environment</li><li>Experience in handling building construction projects will be advantageous</li></ul><p>If this opportunity aligns with your skills and experience, please submit your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p><p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p><p>www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
